A retaining structure of mechanically stabilised
earth obtained by means ofthe insertion of reinforce
ment elements (6, 8) extending perpendicularly to the
equipped with a front facing composed of panels (1-3)
preferably prefabricated in reinforced concrete, to which
the reinforcement elements (6, 8) are secured by means
of an anchorage system (5, 7). The said reinforcement
elements (6, B) are composed of substantially bidimen
sional layers and are, in particular, polymer geogrids or
geotextiles for geotechnical applications, and at least
some of the said layers (6, 8) extend as loops from one
level of earth to the above one, by rising vertically on
the back of the said front facing panels (1-3), or along
the rear part of the said reinforced earth structure, op
c/o Ing. Barzano & Zanardo Roma S.p.A.
